    "collapsible_content_faq_wrist": {
      "type": "collapsible-content",
      "blocks": {
        "faq_wrist_1": {
          "type": "collapsible-row-content",
          "settings": {
            "open": false,
            "heading": "How does the 360° arm trainer actually work?",
            "icon": "",
            "filled_icon": false,
            "row_content": "<p>It uses centrifugal force generated by the rotating mechanism. As you spin the arm cuff in circular motions, the momentum creates resistance that engages your biceps, triceps, and shoulder muscles. The faster and more controlled your rotation, the greater the muscle activation — similar to how a gyroscope creates resistance through inertia.</p>",
            "page": ""
          },
          "blocks": {}
        },
        "faq_wrist_2": {
          "type": "collapsible-row-content",
          "settings": {
            "open": false,
            "heading": "Will this actually help with arm fat and flabbiness?",
            "icon": "",
            "filled_icon": false,
            "row_content": "<p>Yes, with consistent daily use. The rotational resistance targets the muscles underneath the fat — primarily the triceps and shoulders — helping to tone and firm the area over time. Most users notice visible differences within 3-6 weeks of regular use. Results improve when combined with a balanced diet.</p>",
            "page": ""
          },
          "blocks": {}
        },
        "faq_wrist_3": {
          "type": "collapsible-row-content",
          "settings": {
            "open": false,
            "heading": "What do the 3 LCD modes do?",
            "icon": "",
            "filled_icon": false,
            "row_content": "<p>The built-in LCD display tracks your workout data across 3 training modes. Each mode monitors a different combination of revolutions, elapsed time, and estimated calories burned — letting you set goals, track progress, and challenge yourself to improve session by session.</p>",
            "page": ""
          },
          "blocks": {}
        },
        "faq_wrist_4": {
          "type": "collapsible-row-content",
          "settings": {
            "open": false,
            "heading": "Is it suitable for older adults or beginners?",
            "icon": "",
            "filled_icon": false,
            "row_content": "<p>Absolutely. The centrifugal motion is low-impact and joint-friendly, making it suitable for a wide age range including seniors. Beginners can start with short 5-minute sessions at a slow pace and gradually increase as they build strength and confidence.</p>",
            "page": ""
          },
          "blocks": {}
        },
        "faq_wrist_5": {
          "type": "collapsible-row-content",
          "settings": {
            "open": false,
            "heading": "What are the dimensions and weight?",
            "icon": "",
            "filled_icon": false,
            "row_content": "<p>Size: 7.68 in × 6.69 in. Weight: 1.3 lbs. Compact and lightweight enough to keep by your desk, use on the couch, or pack in a travel bag. Battery: button battery included.</p>",
            "page": ""
          },
          "blocks": {}
        },
        "faq_wrist_6": {
          "type": "collapsible-row-content",
          "settings": {
            "open": false,
            "heading": "What colors are available?",
            "icon": "",
            "filled_icon": false,
            "row_content": "<p>Available in White and Pink. All variants feature the same premium polycarbonate build and LCD tracking functionality.</p>",
            "page": ""
          },
          "blocks": {}
        },
        "faq_wrist_7": {
          "type": "collapsible-row-content",
          "settings": {
            "open": false,
            "heading": "What if I'm not happy with my results?",
            "icon": "",
            "filled_icon": false,
            "row_content": "<p>We offer a 90-day money-back guarantee. If you use it consistently and are not satisfied with your experience for any reason, reach out to our team and we will make it right — no questions asked.</p>",
            "page": ""
          },
          "blocks": {}
        }
      },
